# QA Testing & Login

## QA tool

Agent-driven QA on this project uses the Cursor IDE **`cursor-ide-browser` MCP** as the only browser-automation surface. There is **no separate persistent regression suite**; each runbook in `C:\Users\srathjen\.cursor\plans\` is the source of truth for what to test, executed live by the agent.

## Scope

Agent QA covers **desktop and emulated mobile**. Per-runbook scope determines which viewport sizes are required; default to:

- **Desktop:** 1280×800 or wider — full functional coverage
- **Mobile (emulated):** 393×851 via **`browser_resize`** + page reload so responsive breakpoints re-evaluate — layout/regression coverage

**Real touch gestures** (swipe-to-mark-read on notifications, swipe-to-delete on messages, pinch, long-press) cannot be reproduced by the MCP. Verify the visual swipe affordance at 393×851 and document gesture-only behavior as **`AUTOMATION_LIMIT`** in the runbook's live log; surface the item to the human tester for a real-device pass when it matters.

